div.p: REGENSBERG a handſome, though ſmall town of Swiſſerland, in the canton of Zurich, and capital of a bailiwick of the fame name, with a ſtrong caſtle ; ſeat-cd on a hill, which is part of Mount Jura. There is a well ſunk through a rock, 36 fathoms deep.
